.TH DKG\-VERIFY "1" "October 2017" "@PACKAGE_NAME@ @PACKAGE_VERSION@" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
dkg\-verify \- verifies a detached signature according to OpenPGP (only DSA/DSS)

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dkg\-verify
.RI [ options ]
.IR KEYFILE

.SH DESCRIPTION
This program verifies a detached signature read from STDIN according to the OpenPGP standard.
KEYFILE must contain the ASCII-armored public key, for which the verification is performed.
The input file for which the signature was computed is given by the mandatory option "-i".
.PP
The program returns a non-zero value on error; e.g. if the signature is invalid.

.SH OPTIONS
Arguments mandatory for long options are also mandatory for short options.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
print this help
.TP
\fB\-i\fR, \fB\-\-input\fR=\fI\,FILENAME\/\fR
verify detached signature from FILENAME
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
turn on verbose output

.SH "SECURITY"
The current implementation is in experimental state and should NOT be used in
production environments.

